Description:
Ballistics of 30x165mm full caliber rounds fired from autocannons 2A42, 2A72. Barrel length is 2413-2416mm, travel approximated by subtracting length of cartridge. Chambrage chosen to match cartridge length. Grain geometry is assumed. Projectiles includes OFZ (HE-Fragmentation-Incendiary, alternative designations 3UOF8, OF47) and OT (HE-Tracer, 3UOR6, OR2) weigh approximately 390 grams. Cartridge notionally develops 960 m/s (±15 m/s, median deviation <5m/s) from an average maximum chamber pressure of 3500 or 3600 kgf/cm^2 (copper crusher gauge) at 15 °C. However, range table of 3UOR6 list a muzzle velocity of 980 m/s.
